{
  "texts": [
    "descriptions, both prompting and training methods successfully reflect the induced traits in their responses to the personality questionnaires.",
    "Specifically, these methods produce higher scores for high trait levels and lower scores for low trait levels, indicating that the traits are effectively embedded.",
    "However, training-based methods, SFT and DPO, induce more pronounced personality traits than the two prompting-based approaches.",
    "Yet, we find no substantial difference between SFT and DPO.",
    "The training-based methods notably excel in producing lower scores for low levels of personality traits when compared to prompting-based methods."
  ]
}